# Page Plan: Student/Applicant — Notifications

## Route
`/notifications`
*(Accessible via a notification bell icon in the student/applicant navbar)*

## Purpose
A lightweight notification inbox for applicants and students to stay informed about key updates in their application and enrollment journey. Notifications are delivered in real-time via Convex reactive queries.

## Roles Permitted
- `Applicant` — receives notifications about application status changes, payment confirmations, and refunds.
- `Student` — receives all of the above plus enrollment-related notifications.

## UI Layout

1. **Navbar Integration (all applicant/student pages)**:
   - A Bell icon in the top nav bar with an unread count badge.
   - Clicking opens a **dropdown panel** showing the 5 most recent notifications with a "View all →" link.
2. **Full Notifications Page** (`/notifications`):
   - **Page Header** — "Notifications" + "Mark all as read" button.
   - **Filter Tabs** — Unread | All
   - **Notification List** — chronologically ordered:
     - Icon (based on type: ✅ success, ❌ declined, 💰 payment, 📋 enrollment).
     - Title (e.g., "Application Approved").
     - Body (e.g., "Congratulations! Your application has been approved. Begin your enrollment now.").
     - Timestamp (relative, e.g., "2 hours ago").
     - Clickable — navigates to the relevant page.
     - Unread items have a blue dot indicator.
   - **Empty state** — "You're all caught up! No new notifications." with a friendly illustration.

## Notification Types (Student/Applicant-facing)

| Type | Trigger | Title | Body | Links to |
|------|---------|-------|------|----------|
| `application_status_change` | Admin approves application | Application Approved | "Congratulations! Your application has been approved. Begin your enrollment now." | `/enrollment` |
| `application_status_change` | Admin declines application | Application Declined | "Unfortunately, your application was not successful. [Reason excerpt]" | `/application/status` |
| `payment_received` | Application fee payment succeeds | Payment Confirmed | "Your application fee of [amount] has been received." | `/application/status` |
| `payment_refunded` | Auto-refund on decline | Application Fee Refunded | "Your application fee of [amount] has been refunded. Please allow 5–10 business days." | `/application/status` |
| `tuition_payment_received` | Tuition payment succeeds | Tuition Payment Confirmed | "Your tuition payment of [amount] has been received." | `/enrollment` |
| `enrollment_step_complete` | A checklist step is verified | Enrollment Step Completed | "You've completed [Step Name]. Keep going!" | `/enrollment` |
| `enrollment_completed` | All 3 enrollment steps done | Enrollment Complete 🎉 | "Congratulations! You are now fully enrolled as a student." | `/student/dashboard` |

## Behaviour
1. Notification list uses a **reactive Convex query** — updates appear instantly without page refresh.
2. Clicking a notification marks it as read and navigates to the linked page.
3. The unread badge count updates reactively across all pages via a shared query.
4. Notifications older than 90 days are auto-archived (handled by a Convex cron job).

## Data Requirements
- `notifications.listOwn({ filter, cursor })` — paginated list of notifications for the current user.
- `notifications.getUnreadCount()` — reactive query powering the badge across all pages.
- `notifications.markAsRead({ notificationId })` — marks a single notification as read.
- `notifications.markAllAsRead()` — bulk marks all of the current user's notifications as read.

## Navigation
- Bell icon in navbar → dropdown showing latest 5, "View all →" links to `/notifications`.
- Each notification item → linked page based on `relatedEntityType` and `relatedEntityId`.
